06:02.320 --> 06:05.812
And did you know people say
he might've sold his soul to the devil?

06:08.110 --> 06:10.237
Thats what
Cross Road Blues
is about, right?

06:10.370 --> 06:11.519
Uh-huh.

06:13.950 --> 06:15.577
What's wrong with the turnips?

06:17.120 --> 06:18.576
I'm not sure.

06:20.630 --> 06:24.589
Looks like someone swallowed them,
and puked them back up.

06:24.670 --> 06:28.254
Well, look at it this way,
it's one less vegetable you gotta eat.

06:28.340 --> 06:29.295
I like vegetables.

06:30.050 --> 06:31.210
How old are you?

06:32.430 --> 06:34.512
How much food do we have in the pantries?

06:35.270 --> 06:38.433
- Mmm, enough.
- Yeah, but

06:38.520 --> 06:41.557
how long would it last
if it was all we had?

06:41.650 --> 06:46.098
Charlie, you don't need to worry
about stuff like that any more.

06:46.940 --> 06:48.487
You know, we're almost growing enough,

06:49.070 --> 06:51.561
so, we won't have to
go out there for anything.

06:58.370 --> 06:59.667
Come on.

07:01.040 --> 07:02.837
Let's look at the cabbages.

07:03.920 --> 07:05.911
- Charlie's family?
- She said they're out there.

07:06.000 --> 07:08.878
- You got her to talk about it?
- Not exactly. She pointed.

07:08.970 --> 07:09.925
But I checked her book.

07:10.010 --> 07:11.796
It's from the public library
out in Bartlett.

07:11.930 --> 07:14.717
Mmm-mmm. Mmm-mmm.
That's outside the range.

07:14.810 --> 07:17.131
